Today a former USSR Supreme Soviet Deputy from Latvia said the adoption of the 
Latvian citizenship law violates human rights, and creates the conditions for a conflict 
like those in the Caucasus. He said the United States encouraged Latvia to pass the law 
discriminating against the Russian-speaking population of Latvia. He then went on to 
describe a convoluted scenario that has Russia supporting the law in order to create a 
situation that would later benefit Russia at Latvia's expense. He wouldn't or couldn't 
name the sources of the information on which the scenario was built.</SUM>
